\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Workflow for creating block themes\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Once you have learned the basics about block themes, your block theme creation flow will probably look something like this:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Install the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wordpress.org/plugins/create-block-theme/"}}{\fldrslt \ul Create Block Theme plugin}}\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Create a blank theme from the plugin options\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Add a color palette and fonts in the Site Editor 
\f3\i Styles
\f1\i0  panel\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Create block templates based on the desired design\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Export the changes to a theme .zip file\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	6	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Tweak the theme files in your code editor\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	7	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Repeat from step 4\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There are no right or wrong workflows. With some practice, you will find a workflow that suits you. Eventually, you will have created your own starter theme and you will no longer need to use the plugin to create the initial files. You will also likely have a library of pattern and template designs that you can reuse in your themes.\cb1 \
\cb3 However, there are several 
\f3\i gotchas
\f1\i0  when creating block themes, especially if you are comparing them to classic themes. That is why I suggest starting with these five lessons, which will help you understand the basics of block themes and give you a good starting point.\cb1 \
\cb3 You can follow along and create a block theme with me, or use the \'93super quick start guide\'94 and only have this page as a reference.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

