\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Step 1: Create the theme folder and style.css\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 You can expect that the theme setup will be more straightforward and require fewer files in the future. It is even possible that the only file you will need is the new 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cb3  configuration file. But let\'92s look at the theme file structure and block templates required to create block themes today.\cb1 \
\cb3 First, select a theme name and use the slug to create your new theme folder inside\cb1 \uc0\u8232 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 wp-content/themes
\f1\fs32 \cb3 . If your theme name is \'93Lesson One\'94, your folder will be:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf7 \cb8 wp-content/themes/lesson-one
\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Create a 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 style.css
\f1\fs32 \cb3  file in the root folder of the theme. Block themes use a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.wordpress.org/themes/basics/main-stylesheet-style-css/#basic-structure"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul standard style.css file header}}. Copy and paste the following code into the file. Update the fields as needed.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 The only 
\f2\b required
\f1\b0  part of the file header is the theme name.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Start with an empty style.css file\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Your theme will rely on block styles and the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cb3  configuration file as much as possible.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 I suggest starting with an empty 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 style.css
\f1\fs32 \cb3  file, except for the file header. Using an empty 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 style.css
\f1\fs32 \cb3  file is an excellent way to learn the strengths and limitations of 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 theme.json
\f1\fs32 \cb3 .\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Step 2: Add your first block template\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Block templates
\f1\b0  are your base HTML files, and just like PHP files in classic themes, they follow the WordPress template hierarchy.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

