\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Step 4: Include functions.php and theme support (optional)\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Themes do not require a 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 functions.php
\f1\fs32 \cb3  file to work. You can include 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 functions.php
\f1\fs32 \cb3  in your block theme, if you need to enqueue stylesheets or JavaScript, add custom block styles and image sizes, or use hooks.\cb1 \
\cb3 Create a new file in the root folder and name it 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 functions.php
\f1\fs32 \cb3 .\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Next, add the file header, and if you like, enqueue the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 style.css
\f1\fs32 \cb3  file for later use with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/wp_enqueue_style/"}}{\fldrslt 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 \ul wp_enqueue_style()}}:\cb1 \
\cb3 You do not need to enqueue the comment-reply script commonly used in classic themes because the comments block enqueues this automatically.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 Theme support\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 The following theme support is automatically enabled for block themes:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 post-thumbnails, editor-styles, responsive-embeds, automatic-feed-links, html5 styles, and html5 scripts.\cb1 \
\cb3 You do not need to include 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 add_theme_support(\'a0'title-tag'\'a0)
\f1\fs32 \cb3  in the setup function, because WordPress already renders the title tag for full site editing themes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Templates are loaded in the body element\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 WordPress already adds the necessary HTML elements and hooks. The complete code is:\cb1 \
\cb3 If you need to change the meta tags, you need to use hooks and filters.\cb1 \
\cb3 On the front, your templates and all your blocks are loaded in the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 <body>
\f1\fs32 \cb3  element, inside a 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 <div>
\f1\fs32 \cb3  with the class 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb6 wp-site-blocks
\f1\fs32 \cb3 . There is no way to remove this div.\cb1 \
